---
import LegalPageLayout from "../layouts/LegalPageLayout.astro";
---

<LegalPageLayout
  title="Delete your account - CheqSplit"
  description="How to request deletion of your CheqSplit account and associated personal data."
  canonicalPath="/delete-account/"
>
  <article class="legal-doc text-slate-800" aria-labelledby="del-acc-title">
    <header class="mb-10 border-b border-slate-200 pb-8">
      <h1 id="del-acc-title" class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 md:text-4xl">
        Delete your account
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600">
        <strong>Last updated:</strong> April 16, 2026
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-10 text-base leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        This page explains how to request deletion of your CheqSplit account and associated personal data processed by{" "}
        <strong>CheqSplit</strong> (the app listed on Google Play under this developer listing).
      </p>

      <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="how-req">
        <h2 id="how-req" class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">How to request account deletion</h2>
        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-3 pl-6">
          <li>
            Send an email to{" "}
            <a class="font-medium text-brand-600 underline hover:text-brand-700" href="mailto:lungusterus@gmail.com"
              >lungusterus@gmail.com</a
            >
            {" "}from the email address linked to your CheqSplit account (the same email you use for Firebase / Google sign-in, if applicable).
          </li>
          <li>Use the subject line: <strong>Account deletion request</strong>.</li>
          <li>
            In the message, state clearly that you want your CheqSplit account and associated data deleted. If you signed in with Google,
            mention the Google account email so we can match your identity.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p>
          We may reply to confirm your identity before processing the request. If we cannot verify the request, we may ask for additional information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="what-del">
        <h2 id="what-del" class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">What we delete</h2>
        <p>After we process a verified request, we aim to delete or anonymize:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>
            Your authentication profile data held in our backend (e.g. Firebase Authentication user record associated with your account).
          </li>
          <li>
            Your app data stored under your user identifier in our databases (e.g. trips, bills, and related content tied to your account),
            subject to technical and legal constraints below.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="what-keep">
        <h2 id="what-keep" class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">What may be retained (and why)</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-3 pl-6">
          <li><strong>Aggregated or de-identified data</strong> that cannot reasonably be linked back to you.</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Records we must keep</strong> for a limited time where required by law (for example tax, accounting, or fraud-prevention obligations).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Data held only on your device</strong> until you uninstall the app or clear app data; we cannot remotely wipe another user’s phone.
            Other participants may retain copies of shared bills they already received.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Subscription and purchase records</strong> processed by Apple or Google and our payment/subscription providers may be retained according to their policies and legal requirements;
            deleting your CheqSplit account does not delete receipts in App Store / Play billing systems.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="timing">
        <h2 id="timing" class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Timing</h2>
        <p>
          We will process verified deletion requests within a reasonable period, typically within <strong>30 days</strong>, unless a longer period is required by law or exceptional circumstances (e.g. dispute or abuse investigation).
        </p>
      </section>

      <p class="border-t border-slate-200 pt-6 text-sm text-slate-600">
        For general privacy practices, see our{" "}
        <a class="font-medium text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-700" href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <nav class="border-t border-slate-200 pt-8 text-sm text-slate-600" aria-label="Related legal pages">
        <p>
          Related:{" "}
          <a class="font-medium text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-700" href="/delete-data/">Delete your data (without deleting account)</a>,{" "}
          <a class="font-medium text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-700" href="/terms-of-service/">Terms of Service</a>.
        </p>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </article>
</LegalPageLayout>
